Anonymous Thu 05 May 2022 15:38:56 No.47477237 Report
Quoted By:
>>47476932
Ah yeah, combining 2d and 3d can be tricky. It's always going to be influenced by the viewport that you're drawing in, but the top bar will let you lock the drawing plane to a certain axis, or have the strokes be placed relative to something other than the GP object's origin
>>47477129
stroke placement: surface helps if the camera will be static, or the strokes will change every frame, but the lines will look weird from any angle other than the one it was originally drawn in. Sometimes what I do to make sure the lines appear over the top and not warped is just move the GP object really close to the camera, and then parent it to the camera
